Package ca.mcgill.ecse211.liberty

  • Class Summary 
    Class Description
    Capturing
    This class uses the light data from the front light sensor to determine the correct flag to capture by detecting the right color with switching using the front light sensor.
    LightLocalizer
    This class performs localization in 2 primary methodologies and scenarios.
    Navigation
    This class navigates the robot between two points and generate an available path if there is any obstacle along the way.
    Odometer
    This class calculates the odometer infomation which is the location of the robot with respect to certain reference origin.
    OdometryDisplay  
    robotControl
    This class controls the overall behaviour and processes of the robot, in general, the robot localizes using light and ultrasonic sensors first and then drive to the point where the respective crossing method is given, the robot will cross the imaginary river.
    SensorLogger
    This class is used to create and get a log file of data from all the sensor aboard for analytics and debuging purpose.
    sensorPoller
    This class collects data from the sample providers of the ultrasonic sensors and passes the data to the required classes by getter methods for the details, see the Software Docs
    UltrasonicLocalizer
    This class will perform the ultrasonic localization using the falling edge routine.
